-- China Rare Earth to Raise Up to HK$474 Million Selling 120 Million Shares
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-14T15:00:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/china-rare-earth-to-raise-up-to-hk-474-million-selling-120-million-shares.html
China Rare Earth Holdings Ltd . will
raise as much as HK$474 million through the private sale of as
many as 120 million new shares at HK$3.95 each, the company said
in a Hong Kong stock exchange filing today.  Kim Eng Securities (Hong Kong) Ltd. is placing agent for
the sale, China Rare Earth said. The company said it plans to
use the net proceeds of up to HK$455 million as “general
working capital.” Its stock will resume trading in Hong Kong
tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  